Name: django-ventrilo
Author: Ryan Zander 2010

1. Install

These instructions are very basic and do not take into consideration custom configurations.

1.1. Edit "<your_project>/settings.py" and add the following:

     sys.path.insert(0, '/path/to/django-ventrilo')
     INSTALLED_APPS.append('ventrilo')

1.2. Synchronize the database to add django-ventrilo tables (e.g. manage.py syncdb)

1.3. Login to the admin client and configure the ventrilo options.

1.4. Update the Ventrilo server information (e.g. manage.py update_ventrilo).

     Execute this command regularly (e.g. cron) to synchronize information
     between the Ventrilo server and your database.

1.5. Access the data at: http://example.tld/ventrilo
